Former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri's assassination sparked outrage, with Syrian President Bashar Assad condemning it as a "horrible criminal action."
Opposition leaders blamed Syrian and Lebanese governments, demanding Syrian troops withdraw from Lebanon.
Saudi Arabia rejected an international investigation, while France urged Lebanon to bring the perpetrators to justice.
Hariri, a symbol of Lebanon, was mourned by hundreds of thousands.
The assassination strained Lebanon-Syria relations, with accusations against Syria.
Hariri's death in a suicide car bombing led to a somber funeral procession, highlighting the political turmoil and grief in Lebanon.
